<br>
/pet attack &lt;so and so mob&gt;<br>
<br>
pet runs by everything else non-aggro, attacks so and so mob.  granted you have to be close to the mob to do this, but there are zones where you zone in, and although you are far away from the mob because of pathing, it may be in the room next to you and your pet will start running off to find it, aggro it.<br>
<br>
Now if its not a mob that summons, he's gonna come running to the zone line to attack you, where your group waits to smack it down.  thus you've pulled a mob to the zone without any real danger to yourself. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uualdail.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ualdail</A> at: 3/7/02 8:39:46 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ud5aidan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>D5 AidaN</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 53<br> <font color=#333333>(3/15/02 8:52:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=63.topic&index=75>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Brainstorm: List Consequences of Indifferent Pets</span><hr size=1> Mobs have an aggro radious. If this mob comes running back toward you and gets in another mobs aggro radious, that mob is coming too, no matter what your pet may have conned to that mob (at that point, YOUR aggro is what makes the call, if you send the pet into attack a mob which YOU are ally with, if the pet dies and the mob comes after you, it won't aggro other mobs as they will only be indifferent to you, I could be wrong here, please correct me if I am).<br>
<br>
I see this as the only real case in point to indifferent pets being bad. What if you are ally to all giants in Kael, and you send in a pet after a non-summoning mob and then high tail it to the zoneline, because you're ally, shouldn't only the mob the pet attacked follow? <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=34808>Aidonis</a></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32>Class Balance</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
